"title": "8738: evil, victory over",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8738: evil, victory over",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Although evil continues to be present and active in the world, Scripture gives an assurance that God will finally triumph over evil in all its forms.</p>\n<h2>Satan's power is already limited by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:12\">JOB 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:14-Gen3:15\">GEN 3:14–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:6\">JOB 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:2\">ZEC 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:9\">REV 12:9</a></p>\n<h2>Evil spirits are subject to God's control</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:14\">1SA 16:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:23\">JDG 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:10\">1SA 18:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:9\">1SA 19:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:23\">1KI 22:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13-Col2:15\">COL 2:13–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:6\">JUD 1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's triumph over evil powers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:8\">1JN 3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:25-Matt12:29\">MAT 12:25–12:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:23-Mark3:27\">MRK 3:23–3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:17-Luke11:22\">LUK 11:17–11:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:27\">MRK 1:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:36\">LUK 4:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:13\">LUK 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:18\">LUK 10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:31\">JHN 12:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:30\">JHN 14:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14-Heb2:15\">HEB 2:14–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:4\">1JN 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:21\">REV 3:21</a></p>\n<h2>God's transforming power reverses the effects of evil in human lives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2\">1JN 3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:10\">JON 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:15\">MRK 5:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:35\">LUK 8:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:17-Acts26:18\">ACT 26:17–26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:14\">ROM 6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:10\">1CO 15:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:9\">2CO 12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:10\">COL 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>God brings good out of evil</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:20\">GEN 50:20</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:28\">ROM 8:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:8\">GEN 45:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job23:10\">JOB 23:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:3\">JHN 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:24\">JHN 12:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:36\">ACT 2:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13-Acts3:16\">ACT 3:13–3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:30-Acts5:31\">ACT 5:30–5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:12-Phil1:14\">PHP 1:12–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:17-Phil1:18\">PHP 1:17–1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:2-Jas1:3\">JAS 1:2–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:6-1Pet1:7\">1PE 1:6–1:7</a></p>\n<h2>The removal of the curse on creation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:20-Rom8:21\">ROM 8:20–8:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:28\">MAT 19:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:21\">ACT 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1\">REV 21:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:5\">REV 21:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:3\">REV 22:3</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's victory over evil is expressed in his thousand-year reign with believers, during which Satan is bound</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4\">REV 20:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:2\">REV 20:2</a> <em>Interpreters differ over whether the “thousand years” refers to a future period or to Jesus Christ's present rule in the world.</em></p>\n<h2>The final defeat of all evil powers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:4\">REV 20:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:20\">ROM 16:20</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:10\">REV 20:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:1\">MAL 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:41-Matt13:42\">MAT 13:41–13:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:41\">MAT 25:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:25\">1CO 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:8\">2TH 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:20\">REV 19:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a></p>\n<h2>Evil will be excluded from the new heaven and earth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:13\">2PE 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:17\">ISA 65:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:4\">REV 21:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:27\">REV 21:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:15\">REV 22:15</a></p>",
